<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,158,257]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,302,158,184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The species is named in honor of the late Dr V.B. Hosagoudar, a renowned fungal taxonomist and a guiding force for many students and researchers in the country and also for his outstanding contribution in the field of foliar mycobionts in 
<collectingCountry box="[370,430,230,256]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">India</collectingCountry>
, over three decades.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6375219" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6375219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6375219/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" startId="2.[136,229,1675,1697]" targetBox="[169,1405,288,1626]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1453,1675,1733]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,247,1675,1697]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">FIGURE 1</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Sabeena &amp; H. Biju" authorityYear="2022" box="[259,533,1675,1696]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="veebeehosagoudarii">
<emphasis box="[259,533,1675,1696]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Meliola veebeehosagoudarii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. a. Appressorium. b. Phialide. c. Apical portion of the mycelial setae. d. Ascospores. Illustrator: Aliyarukunju Sabeena.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1773,2088]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis box="[189,289,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Colonies</emphasis>
epiphyllous, thin to subdense up to 
<quantity box="[678,740,1773,1799]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in diameter, confluent. Hyphae straight to substraight, branching opposite at acute to wide angles, loosely reticulate, cells 17–32 × 5–7 μm. Appressoria opposite to unilateral, antrorse, subantrorse to retrorse, 10–15 μm long; stalk cells cylindrical to cuneate, 2–5 μm long; head cells ovate, oblong, subglobose to globose, entire, 7–10 × 5–10 μm. Phialides mixed with appressoria, opposite, ampulliform, 17–27 × 5–7 μm. Mycelial setae scattered, simple, straight, acute to obtuse at the tip, up to 950 μm long. Perithecia scattered, globose, up to 150 μm in diam. Ascospores oblong, 4-septate, constricted at the septa, 32–37 × 10–12 μm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1773,2088]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1451,158,257]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,256,1989,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authority="Yamam." authorityName="Yamam." box="[292,574,1989,2015]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="heliciae">
<emphasis box="[292,474,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Meliola heliciae</emphasis>
Yamam.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hansf." authorityName="Hansf." box="[583,801,1989,2015]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="banksiae">
<emphasis box="[583,718,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">M. banksiae</emphasis>
Hansf.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pat." authorityName="Pat." box="[810,971,1989,2015]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lanosa">
<emphasis box="[810,920,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">M. lanosa</emphasis>
Pat.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(McAlpine) Hansf." authorityName="Hansf." baseAuthorityName="McAlpine" box="[981,1448,1989,2016]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="lanosa" variety="funerea">
<emphasis box="[981,1091,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">M. lanosa</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1143,1228,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">funerea</emphasis>
(McAlpine) Hansf.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hansf." authorityName="Hansf." box="[136,370,2025,2051]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="grevilleae">
<emphasis box="[136,285,2025,2051]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">M. grevilleae</emphasis>
Hansf.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="B. Huguenin" authorityName="B. Huguenin" box="[381,792,2025,2051]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="grevilleae-gillivrayi">
<emphasis box="[381,642,2025,2051]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">M. grevilleae-gillivrayi</emphasis>
B. Huguenin
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hansf." authorityName="Hansf." box="[848,1087,2025,2051]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="heliciicola">
<emphasis box="[848,1004,2025,2051]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">M. heliciicola</emphasis>
Hansf.
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[1101,1184,2025,2051]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,224,530,556]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparative account of Meliola species known on members of Proteaceae." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF526080FB5EFF9142967B2D3A7F5632" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" tableUuid="DF526080FB5EFF9142967B2D3A7F5632">Table 1</tableCitation>
) are the known species on members of 
<taxonomicName box="[320,441,2061,2087]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Proteaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Proteales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Proteaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hansford, C. G." box="[458,632,2061,2087]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" pagination="1 - 806" refId="ref3411" refString="Hansford, C. G. (1961) The Meliolineae. A monograph. Sydowia Annales Mycologici, Ser. 2: 1 - 806." type="book chapter" year="1961">Hansford 1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Huguenin, B." box="[647,827,2061,2088]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" pagination="23 - 61" refId="ref3884" refString="Huguenin, B. (1969) Micromycetes du Pacifique Sud VII. Meliolinees de Nouvelle-Caledonie 34 (1): 23 - 61." type="journal article" year="1969">Huguenin 1969</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Sabeena &amp; H. Biju" authorityYear="2022" box="[968,1234,2061,2087]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="veebeehosagoudarii">
<emphasis box="[968,1234,2061,2087]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">M. veebeehosagoudarii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all of these in having predominantly opposite appressoria and smaller ascospores. 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1190,158,184]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="banksiae">
<emphasis box="[996,1190,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Meliola banksiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has about 3% opposite appressoria but differs in having 2–3 dentate mycelial setae. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Hansford, C. G." box="[966,1154,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 806" refId="ref3411" refString="Hansford, C. G. (1961) The Meliolineae. A monograph. Sydowia Annales Mycologici, Ser. 2: 1 - 806." type="book chapter" year="1961">Hansford (1961)</bibRefCitation>
, the other species reported on the family 
<taxonomicName box="[292,416,231,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Proteaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Proteales" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Proteaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Speg." authorityName="Speg." box="[428,679,230,256]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Meliola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rupalae">
<emphasis box="[428,609,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Meliola rupalae</emphasis>
Speg.
</taxonomicName>
has been synonymised under 
<taxonomicName authority="(Speg.) F. Stevens." authorityName="F. Stevens." baseAuthorityName="Speg." box="[1016,1430,230,257]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Irenopsis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rupalae">
<emphasis box="[1016,1213,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Irenopsis rupalae</emphasis>
(Speg.) F. Stevens.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
